# Key Product Decisions

This document captures major architectural and product decisions taken during MVP development.

---

# Decision 1 — Prompt-Level Disclaimer Enforcement

### Problem

UI disclaimers can be bypassed.

### Decision

Disclaimer embedded inside system prompt.

### Reason

Healthcare requires stronger safety controls.

### Outcome

Improved governance and reduced misuse risk.

---

# Decision 2 — SQL Lookup Instead of Vector Search

### Problem

Approximate retrieval in healthcare can be unsafe.

### Decision

Drug interactions handled through SQL exact lookup.

### Reason

Medical accuracy is non-negotiable.

### Outcome

Reduced ambiguity.

Improved reliability.

---

# Decision 3 — Low Temperature (0.3)

### Problem

High creativity increases hallucination risk.

### Decision

Temperature restricted to 0.3.

### Reason

Deterministic outputs preferred.

### Outcome

More consistent medical responses.

---

# Decision 4 — Single Chunk Per Drug

### Problem

Splitting medicine information risks incomplete retrieval.

### Decision

One medicine = one chunk.

### Reason

Avoid fragmented medical understanding.

### Outcome

Improved retrieval completeness.

---

# Decision 5 — No Dosage Recommendation

### Problem

Unsafe medical behavior risk.

### Decision

Hard refusal for dosage advice.

### Reason

Avoid healthcare misuse.

### Outcome

Safer AI behavior.
